<HEADLINE>
<P>
U.S. MISSION IN THE GULF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Alexander Cockburn's article "Stand Fast for Talk, Not Battle" is excellent 
(Column Left, Commentary, Oct. 21). 
</P>
<P>
I agree we should say no to Iraq's grab of Kuwait, no to a U.S. war and no to 
double standards about which land grabs and invasions the U.S. chooses to 
denounce. I believe we should say yes to the countries and to the United 
Nations who are trying their utmost to remedy the complex issues in the Persian 
Gulf with a peaceful settlement. 
</P>
<P>
A war wouldn't settle the difficult problems in the area. A war would just 
delay the settlement of international difficulties. The American people don't 
want war with its unbelievable horrors and inhumanities for all concerned. 
</P>
<P>
JEAN M. NICHOLSON 
</P>
<P>
Altadena 
</P>
</TEXT>
