<HEADLINE>
<P>
MUSICAL STANDARDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I wish to respond to some of the recent letters depicting Martin Bernheimer as 
jaded and an overcritical critic. Although, as we know, it is his job to give 
an objective and critiqued account of the operas we all so love, it is also his 
job to pillar high standards of the stage, to keep Mozart Mozart and not Piggly 
Wiggly pop. 
</P>
<P>
I found the "dreamscape" sequence and 16th-Century wigs in "Idomeneo" a little 
too cute. 
</P>
<P>
I have never found Bernheimer vicious, or perhaps I have never found him 
vicious enough. His critiques are always constructive. That is, something could 
be done to improve the play. 
</P>
<P>
In my opinion, Los Angeles and the Los Angeles Times are fortunate to have him. 
</P>
<P>
ALLAN MacMORRES, Woodland Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
