<P>
HEAVY CRITICISM UNFAIR TO 'CALIFORNIA LIGHT' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In spite of Cathy Curtis' flippant "Ho-Hum" critique, I went to see the exhibit 
and I found it beautiful! 
</P>
<P>
A good art critic puts aside his or her personal preferences when judging art. 
Curtis does not do this. She uses ridicule and should stop her silly comments 
about "expecting a broadly sociological look at the connection between art and 
sun-dazzled land." 
</P>
<P>
You owe an apology to these fine artists of another era, when beauty was not 
ridiculed. 
</P>
<P>
MRS. ALBERT AUKERS, Laguna Niguel 
</P>
