<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
TEXAS; 
</P>
<P>
JURY RULES AGAINST WOMAN IN PRIEST SUIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Houston jury refused to find the Roman Catholic Church negligent in a 
$7-million suit filed by a woman who had had a two-year sexual relationship 
with a priest. 
</P>
<P>
Jurors deliberated just three hours before rejecting the claim of Debbie 
McCorvey, 34, that the church was negligent in allowing Father Fernando Noe 
Guzman to exploit her dependence on him as a counselor. McCorvey, a religion 
teacher, claimed church officials were at fault for not making sure Guzman, 39, 
received therapy after his alleged sexual involvement with a 13-year-old girl. 
Church officials argued that McCorvey's relationship with Guzman was 
consensual. 
</P>
</TEXT>
