<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
TEXAS; 
</P>
<P>
WOMAN ACQUITTED OF USING MEN'S ROOM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A woman who said she was desperate when she went to the men's room at a concert 
was found not guilty of illegally using the restroom. 
</P>
<P>
Jurors deliberated for 23 minutes before acquitting Denise Wells of violating a 
Houston ordinance that prohibits people from using restrooms intended for 
members of the opposite sex in a manner calculated to cause a disturbance. She 
faced a maximum $200 fine if convicted of the misdemeanor. Wells testified that 
the women's room line was so long that "I felt I was in a situation where I had 
to be in a restroom. I took the only option I felt was available." 
</P>
</TEXT>
