<TEXT>
<P>
A San Diego bar owner was arrested and her business shut down by undercover 
narcotics agents who made drug buys out of her 16th Street bar, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Narcotics agents from the San Diego Police Department and the state's 
Department of Alcoholic Beverage Control seized 84.75 grams of marijuana and 
$1,614 in cash from the Nayarit Bar at 71 16th St. about 7:30 p.m. Thursday, 
police spokesman Bill Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
