<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: NIGHTCLUB FIRE DAMAGE ESTIMATED AT $350,000 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A fire that started Friday morning in the bar area of a Northridge nightclub 
caused an estimated $350,000 in damage, the Los Angeles Fire Department 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
There were no injuries in the fire, reported at 3:45 a.m. at the Fantasia West 
Nightclub in the 19400 block of Nordhoff Street, firefighter Pat Marek said. 
The nightclub closed more than an hour earlier. 
</P>
<P>
Marek said about 40 firefighters contained the blaze in half an hour. The cause 
of the fire was under investigation. 
</P>
