<P>
RANGER HOME STREAK ENDED AT 8 GAMES BY ISLANDERS, 3-2 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The New York Islanders blew an early two-goal lead before ending the New York 
Rangers' record 8-0 home ice start with a 3-2 victory Friday night on 
defenseman Joe Reekie's first goal of the season at 5:40 of the third period. 
</P>
<P>
Reekie's screen shot from the right point went between the pads of goalie John 
Vanbiesbrouck, who had won his last six starts. 
</P>
<P>
Glenn Healy, the Islanders' goalie, stopped 29 shots, including Mike Gartner's 
breakaway with 25 seconds to play. The Rangers outshot the Islanders, 15-5, in 
the third period. 
</P>
<P>
The Rangers (11-4-0) were 11-1 in their last 12 games and lead the league with 
22 points. The Islanders improved to 4-9-0. 
</P>
