<HEADLINE>
<P>
CAL STATE FULLERTON PLAYS AT SAN JOSE STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE DiGIOVANNA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The longest losing streak in Cal State Fullerton football history is expected 
to continue tonight at 6 when the Titans play at San Jose State in a Big West 
Conference game. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton, which has lost eight in a row since a season-opening victory over 
Sonoma State, has won five of the last seven games against the Spartans, 
including a 58-13 victory in 1988 and a 28-14 win last season. 
</P>
<P>
But San Jose State (5-2-1, 4-0 in conference play) is an overwhelming favorite. 
The Spartans are four points away from an undefeated season. They tied 
25th-ranked Louisville, 10-10, lost to seventh-ranked Washington, 20-17, and 
lost to California, 35-34. MIKE DiGIOVANNA 
</P>
