<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHAMBERS SCORES 38 TO LEAD SUNS TO EASY VICTORY OVER JAZZ IN TOKYO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Phoenix Suns, led by Tom Chambers, started the NBA season half a world away 
from home Friday night with a 119-96 victory over the Utah Jazz in the first 
regular-season NBA game held outside North America. 
</P>
<P>
A sellout crowd of 10,111 at Tokyo Metropolitan Gymnasium, paying as much as 
$175 a seat, was predominantly young Japanese. 
</P>
<P>
The game was close during the first half before the Suns pulled away with a 
19-2 run late in the third quarter, giving Phoenix an 85-70 lead that was never 
threatened. 
</P>
<P>
Chambers scored eight of his 38 points during the run. He scored 27 points in 
the second half when the Suns outscored the Jazz, 61-39, after leading only by 
one at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
Karl Malone led the Jazz with 33 points, 26 in the first half. 
</P>
