DASH FOR SPEED HEADS FIELD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dash For Speed, the leading contender for 1990 World Champion Running Quarter 
Horse honors, heads a field of six fillies and mares in tonight's $25,000 
Charger Bar Handicap at Los Alamitos. 
</P>
<P>
The 350-yard race is the ninth of a 12-race program. 
</P>
<P>
Dash For Speed, a winner of 21 of 27 starts with earnings of $1,093,441, will 
be making her first start since July 28 when she won the Los Alamitos 
Invitational. Kip Didericksen will be aboard. 
</P>
<P>
Her rivals include Wicked Wind, ridden by Luke Myles; Isaws Sugar Bear, Steve 
Treasure; Agua Treasure, John Creager; Winning Guarantee, Alvin Brossette, and 
Brace It Well, Danny Cardoza. 
