<HEADLINE>
<P>
USIU BALLET TROUPE TO APPEAR IN POWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The International Ballet of United States International University will perform 
at 8 p.m. Nov. 9 and at 2 and 4 p.m. Nov. 10 at the Poway Center for the 
Performing Arts. 
</P>
<P>
The four-piece program, which will be the first appearance at the North County 
venue by the university's ensemble, will include three of Elizabeth Rowe 
Wistrich's recent works ("Straw Feet," Samuel Barber Adagio and Concerti), and 
James Kelly's big-band theater piece, "Swing." 
</P>
<P>
USIU's International Orchestra will accompany the Samuel Barber Adagio at all 
three performances. 
</P>
