<P>
HONDURAS TO FIRE WORKERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TEGUCIGALPA, Honduras 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Honduran government will fire as many as 10,000 of its 60,000 state workers 
as part of a severe economic austerity plan launched in April, officials said 
Friday. The workers will be dismissed in January, 1991, in an attempt to reduce 
the Central American nation's $117-million fiscal deficit, a government 
spokesman said. 
</P>
