<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 5 FINALISTS FOR CHILDREN'S SERVICES 
DIRECTOR CHOSEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The search for a new director of the Los Angeles County Department of 
Children's Services has come down to five candidates, all men, all high-ranking 
officials at government social service agencies, and none from California. 
</P>
<P>
The finalists were chosen by a panel of social services and management experts 
after a private search firm examined several hundred applications, according to 
Martin Golds of the county administrator's office. 
</P>
<P>
The Board of Supervisors will interview the five and make the final selection. 
</P>
<P>
The candidates are C. Patrick Babcock, director of the Michigan Department of 
Social Services; Gene E. Daniel, regional director of the Texas Department of 
Human Services; Gerald P. Digre, deputy secretary for operations of the Florida 
Department of Health and Rehabilitation Services; Philip W. Johnston, 
Massachusetts secretary of Human Services, and Michael W. Weber, director of 
the Hennepin County Community Services Department in Minnesota. 
</P>
</TEXT>
