<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: GILLESPIE UNDER REVIEW FOR QUALIFICATION AS 
JUDGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gov. George Deukmejian has submitted Insurance Commissioner Roxani Gillespie's 
name to the state Bar's Commission on Judicial Nominees Evaluation for their 
opinion on whether she is qualified to be named a Los Angeles Superior Court 
judge. 
</P>
<P>
A member of the commission who disclosed this, but asked not to be identified, 
said that the action means that Gillespie probably will be appointed if the 
commission decides she is qualified. 
</P>
<P>
A spokeswoman for Deukmejian said the governor's office would have no comment. 
</P>
<P>
Gillespie, the last appointed insurance commissioner before the job becomes an 
elective post in January, said last winter when she decided not to run for the 
post that she would not return to an insurance industry job. Before she was 
appointed, she had been counsel to a company. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
GILLESPIE, ROXANI M; CALIFORNIA -- JUDGES; POLITICAL APPOINTMENTS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
