<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALABASAS HANDS FILLMORE FIRST LOSS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By NORM WEBER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Damon Riggins scored on a 14-yard run with 5 minutes 12 seconds left and 
Calabasas High upset previously unbeaten Fillmore, 13-7, in a Frontier League 
game Friday night at Calabasas. 
</P>
<P>
Riggins, a senior tailback, rushed for 149 yards in 26 carries and also played 
the entire game on defense. 
</P>
<P>
In addition, he was the team's kicker and connected on one of two extra points. 
Only 14 players suited up for Calabasas (3-6 overall, 1-2 in league play). 
</P>
<P>
Fillmore (8-1, 2-1) took a 7-0 lead late in the first half on a 19-yard run by 
Val Pillado, but Calabasas tied the score in the third quarter on a seven-yard 
keeper by quarterback Ron Adelman. 
</P>
<P>
Early in the fourth quarter, Mike Baron of Calabasas intercepted a pass and 
returned the ball to the Fillmore 27-yard line. Calabasas drove to the 10, but 
a fumble was recovered by Fillmore's Gabe Martinez. 
</P>
<P>
Fillmore was forced to punt five plays later, however, and Calabasas began the 
winning drive. Riggins broke over the left side for a 17-yard gain on the 
second play, and four plays later he burst over the middle, shook off two 
tacklers and romped into the end zone. 
</P>
<P>
Adelman passed for 90 yards, completing nine of 13 passes. He also rushed for 
42 yards and played the entire game as a defensive back. 
</P>
<P>
Pillado finished with 48 rushing yards for Fillmore. Tailback Tory Cabral, who 
has rushed for 978 yards this season, carried only three times for six yards. 
NORM WEBER 
</P>
</TEXT>
