<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROYAL REPEATS IN WATER POLO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Royal and Harvard high water polo teams ended their league seasons Friday 
in championship form. 
</P>
<P>
Royal, which has won 10 consecutive Marmonte League titles, put the finishing 
touches on another undefeated league season with a 16-4 victory over Newbury 
Park. Rob Martin had four goals for Royal (20-3, 10-0), which has not lost a 
league match since 1986 and has a 38-match league winning streak. 
</P>
<P>
Harvard trounced visiting St. Francis, 27-5, to finish 20-6, 7-1 and in a tie 
for first place in the San Fernando Valley League with Crespi. Ryan Salceda led 
Harvard with six goals. Teammate Jim Toring missed the match because of 
illness. 
</P>
</TEXT>
