<P>
Brokerage Fee Case to Go to Jury: Arguments in a suit over a disputed 
multimillion-dollar brokerage fee ended in Orange County Superior Court in 
Santa Ana, and the jury is expected to begin deliberations Monday. Real estate 
broker Lee &amp; Associates alleges that it was cheated out of a $9-million 
commission when Fluor Corp. sold its Irvine headquarters to Trammell Crow Co. 
in 1985. Lee is seeking $64 million in restitution and damages against Fluor, 
the giant engineering and construction company, and Trammell Crow, one of the 
nation's top commercial developers. 
