<HEADLINE>
<P>
ESPERANZA CLINCHES TIE FOR TITLE WITH 42-0 VICTORY OVER CYPRESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DALE RUHE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANAHEIM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jarod Smith rushed for two touchdowns, and Keith McDonald threw for two more as 
Esperanza High School defeated Cypress, 42-0, Friday in an Empire League 
football game in front of about 500 at Western High School. 
</P>
<P>
The Aztecs had 313 yards in total offense as they clinched a tie for the league 
championship. 
</P>
<P>
They can win the title outright next Friday with a victory over Katella. 
Esperanza, top-ranked and the only undefeated team in Division III, is 9-0, 4-0 
in league play. 
</P>
<P>
Smith scored his first touchdown on a 15-yard run with 4 minutes 43 seconds 
left in the first quarter. He scored again with 10:11 left in the first half on 
a 20-yard run. The second score was set up when Cypress quarterback Gabe Garcia 
fumbled, and the Aztecs' Mike Burns recovered at the Cypress 40. 
</P>
<P>
McDonald completed a 13-yard scoring pass to Ryan Corbett with 1:26 left in the 
first half, and Esperanza led at the break, 21-0. McDonald came back with a 
20-yard scoring pass to tight end Reid Pullen with 7:05 left in the third 
quarter. DALE RUHE 
</P>
</TEXT>
