<HEADLINE>
<P>
DANA HILLS' BIG SECOND HALF STOPS SAN CLEMENTE, 37-27 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN CLEMENTE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Marcus Jenkins intercepted two passes and ran for a touchdown to lead Dana 
Hills to a 37-27 victory over San Clemente in a South Coast League game Friday 
night at San Clemente. 
</P>
<P>
Jenkins, a junior, helped the Dolphins (4-4-1, 1-3) rally from a 20-10 
second-quarter deficit. 
</P>
<P>
San Clemente (4-5, 0-4 in league) led early behind the passing of Ken Dolan and 
the running of Shane Shanafelt. 
</P>
<P>
Dolan threw a nine-yard touchdown pass to Chris Carroll on the first series, 
and Shanafelt had 42 yards in his first two carries. 
</P>
<P>
Dana Hills' John Ashley kicked a 32-yard field goal to cut the deficit to 7-3. 
</P>
<P>
After an 11-yard touchdown run by Shanafelt made it 13-3, Nick Nosek ran eight 
yards for a touchdown, making it 13-10 in the second quarter. An interception 
by Jenkins set up the score. 
</P>
<P>
Morgan Bannister gave San Clemente a 20-10 lead on a six-yard touchdown run, 
but Dana Hills responded with a six-yard touchdown run by Shaun Coleman to make 
it 20-17 at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
Dana Hills then outscored San Clemente, 20-0, on touchdown runs by Jenkins and 
Nosek and two field goals by Ashley. 
</P>
</TEXT>
