<DATELINE>
<P>
TUSTIN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ben Rooker of Trabuco Hills High School scored two touchdowns to lead the 
Mustangs to a 34-0 victory over Century in a Pacific Coast League game Friday 
night at Tustin High. 
</P>
<P>
Rooker, a 6-4, 225-pound running back, rushed for 71 yards in 14 carries for 
Trabuco Hills (4-4-1, 3-1 in league) over the hapless Centurions. 
</P>
<P>
Century (3-6, 1-3) was held to 62 yards rushing and Centurion quarterback Stacy 
De La Monte completed two of 11 passes for nine yards. 
</P>
<P>
Trabuco Hills' sophomore Pat Barnes shared quarterback duties with senior Shane 
Weintraut. Barnes completed four of six passes for 119 yards while Weintraut 
was six of 10 for 79 yards. 
</P>
<P>
Rooker scored the Mustangs first touchdown five minutes into the first quarter 
on a two-yard run that capped a 73-yard drive. Kicker Jason Teno's extra point 
was good, giving Trabuco Hills a 7-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
Rooker scored again with 3:37 left in the second quarter on a five-yard run as 
the Mustangs' took a 21-0 lead into the locker room at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
Barnes hit Nick Pavaroff on a 48-yard pass play to increase the Mustangs' lead 
to 27-0. KIM KUTCHER 
