<HEADLINE>
<P>
IRELAND FINISHES COMEBACK FOR SANTA MARGARITA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By VINCE AGUL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MISSION VIEJO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Josh Ireland's three-yard run with 1:56 left in the game gave Santa Margarita a 
35-31 victory over San Luis Obispo in front of 1,000 fans Friday at Saddleback 
College Field. Santa Margarita (9-0) scored 28 second-half points to earn the 
nonleague victory. 
</P>
<P>
Trailing, 14-7 at halftime, Santa Margarita scored four touchdowns in the 
second half, including a 90-yard kickoff return by Ireland. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Margarita's other second-half touchdowns came on a 19-yard run by 
quarterback Trevor Yankoff and a 27-yard run by halfback Mike Farris. San Luis 
Obispo had built a 31-21 lead before Farris' fourth-quarter scoring run made it 
31-28, setting the stage for Ireland's 16th touchdown of the year. 
</P>
<P>
San Luis Obispo (3-6) took the opening kickoff and went 70 yards on 12 plays to 
score. Quarterback David Beauchamp completed a 17-yard pass to David DeLange 
for a 7-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
Five plays later, Santa Margarita tied the game on a 62-yard touchdown pass 
from Yankoff to David Shearer. 
</P>
<P>
With 41 seconds left in the first half, San Luis Obispo made it 14-7 when 
Beauchamp passed 35 yards to Mark Quarles. VINCE AGUL 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
