<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
VILLA PARK BEATS MISSION VIEJO IN WATER POLO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Villa Park High School withstood a fourth-quarter charge and defeated Mission 
Viejo, 8-7, in a nonleague water polo game Friday at Villa Park. 
</P>
<P>
Fourth-ranked Villa Park led, 5-2, with just over two minutes left in the third 
quarter before Mission Viejo made a charge to pull within 6-5 with 2:30 
remaining. The teams traded goals from that point, and Villa Park was able to 
hang on. 
</P>
<P>
Kip Parsons had four goals, and Josh Woolery had two for Villa Park (20-6). 
</P>
<P>
In another nonleague game: 
</P>
<P>
Esperanza 13, Loyola 11 -- Mark Campagna had nine goals for host Esperanza 
(11-11). Craig Thomas had 10 saves for Esperanza. 
</P>
<P>
In Angelus League water polo: 
</P>
<P>
Servite 13, Santa Margarita 4 -- Servite (11-3, 6-2) qualified for Southern 
Section 3-A playoffs for the first time in five years. Justin Daniels scored 
two goals. 
</P>
<P>
In Orange League water polo: 
</P>
<P>
Brea-Olinda 21, Western 7 -- Bryan Noyes had four goals, and Scott Kling and 
Chad Carlberg each had three for visiting Brea-Olinda (20-5, 9-1), which won 
the league championship and passed the 1987 school record for season victories. 
</P>
<P>
In Pacific Coast League girls' volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Beach 3, Trabuco Hills 0 -- Kealy Clarke had 24 assists, and Ashley 
Wacholder had 11 kills to lead second-ranked Laguna Beach (19-4, 10-0) to a 
15-3, 15-0, 15-1 victory. Laguna Beach has gone undefeated in league for two 
consecutive seasons. 
</P>
<P>
In Academy League girls' volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
St. Margaret's 3, Inland Christian 1 -- Shannon Carroll had nine kills and two 
aces, and Hilary Albers had 15 assists and four aces to lead St. Margaret's 
(14-6, 6-0) to a 16-14, 14-16, 15-11, 15-10 victory and clinch the league 
title. 
</P>
<P>
In South Coast League girls' tennis: 
</P>
<P>
El Toro 11, Irvine 7 -- El Toro's No. 1 doubles team of Denise Kenyon and 
Jessica Ledford and No. 2 doubles team of Carrie Anderson and Joclyn Jespersen 
swept their matches as the Chargers won a playoff for third place in the 
league. 
</P>
<P>
In Sunset League girls' individual tennis: 
</P>
<P>
Urricariet wins singles -- Renee Urricariet of Fountain Valley defeated 
teammate Michelle Berkowitz, 4-6, 6-2, 6-2, for the singles championship at 
Lindborg Racquet Club in Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
In doubles, Marisa Mell and Nora Kapche of Fountain Valley defeated Jennifer 
Johnson and Courtney Woods of Huntington Beach, 5-7, 6-2, 6-3, for the title. 
</P>
</TEXT>
