<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
MENDIOLA'S HAT TRICK LEADS IRVINE VALLEY MEN PAST GOLDEN WEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Peiro Mendiola scored three goals to lead Irvine Valley to a 6-1 victory over 
Golden West Friday in an Orange Empire Conference men's soccer game at Golden 
West. 
</P>
<P>
Ryan Tinsley had two goals and Brad Wilson one for Irvine Valley (13-1-5, 8-1-3 
in conference). 
</P>
<P>
Ryan Sherry scored for Golden West (7-9-3, 5-4-3). 
</P>
<P>
Aaron Ryan had 10 saves for Irvine Valley, and Chris Lekavich had seven for 
Golden West. 
</P>
<P>
In another Orange Empire League soccer match: 
</P>
<P>
Cypress 3, Fullerton 0 -- Charlie Higley, George Charlesworth and Earl Norman 
scored for host Cypress. 
</P>
<P>
In the South Coast Conference water polo tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Golden West 21, Fullerton 4 -- Dave Johnson, Edvard Van Luijin and Tory 
Culbertson scored three goals each for Golden West (25-3) in the semifinal 
match at Belmont Plaza in Long Beach. Golden West plays in the championship 
game at 7:30 tonight at Belmont Plaza. 
</P>
<P>
In Orange Empire Conference water polo: 
</P>
<P>
Saddleback 17, Rancho Santiago 13 -- Bobby Killin' scored five goals and Jason 
Armison, Matt Dunbar and Omar Ward three each for Saddleback (9-18, 4-8) in the 
final game of the year. 
</P>
<P>
In Orange Empire Conference women's soccer 
</P>
<P>
Palomar 3, Golden West 1 -- Melanie Midani scored five minutes into the second 
half for visiting Golden West (7-7-2, 3-3-1) to briefly tie the score. Heather 
Armstrong, Allison Gibson and Erin Merrifield scored for Palomar. 
</P>
<P>
In Orange Empire Conference women's volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
Golden West 3, Cypress 0 -- Brenda Irby had 16 kills and Kysha Green 10 for 
Golden West (14-1, 9-0) in a 15-2, 15-7, 15-10 victory at Cypress. Kari 
Calliham had nine kills for Cypress (8-5, 4-5). 
</P>
</TEXT>
