<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPOTLIGHT / COMMERCIAL REAL ESTATE: FOCUS: TRIANGLE SQUARE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Triangle Square, a $60-million retail and entertainment complex, is being built 
as part of Costa Mesa's redevelopment program. The Mediterranean-style building 
will feature restaurants, shops, an eight-screen cinema and a 
40,000-square-foot supermarket. 
</P>
<P>
Also included will be a half-acre Town Square, an open-air courtyard where 
entertainment and community events will be held. 
</P>
<P>
FACTS AND FIGURES 
</P>
<P>
Address: Harbor Boulevard, Newport Boulevard and 19th Street, Costa Mesa 
</P>
<P>
Owner/Developer: Joint venture of Triangle Square Associates &amp; Capital and 
Counties USA Inc. 
</P>
<P>
Architect: Altoon &amp; Porter, Los Angeles 
</P>
<P>
Contractor: Keller Construction, El Monte 
</P>
<P>
Financing: Dai-Ichi Kangyo Bank, Los Angeles and Citicorp Real Estate, Costa 
Mesa 
</P>
<P>
Scheduled opening: Spring, 1992 
</P>
<P>
Total acreage: 4.5 
</P>
<P>
Leasable space in square feet: 185,000 
</P>
<P>
Parking capacity: 1,160 
</P>
<P>
Source: The Bower Agency Inc. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Drawing, Triangle Square 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
